name: Emily Wenger
content: Emily Wenger I am an Assistant Professor of Electrical and Computer Engineering at Duke University, where I run the ARGUS Lab. Our lab researches topics related to AI, security, and society. I obtained my PhD from the University of Chicago. My research has been featured by numerous media outlets including CNN, NBC, the New York Times, and I was named to the 2024 Forbes 30 under 30 list for my work on Glaze, a tool that protects artists' work from unwanted use in generative AI models.
